l_main_2532484\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tqs1665703533353.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tqs1665703533353.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tqs1665703533353.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tqs1665703533353\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"tqs1665703533353__wildcards_in_parameters_519768\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A number of the command line switches recognize a limited set of wildcards in\n      parameters.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"tqs1665703533353__table_d18545e1_d18546e1_d18547e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Wildcards for Parameters of Command Line Switches</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"tqs1665703533353__table_d18545e1_d18546e1_d18547e1__entry__1\">\n Wildcard\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"tqs1665703533353__table_d18545e1_d18546e1_d18547e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tqs1665703533353__table_d18545e1_d18546e1_d18547e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">*</code>  or <code class=\"ph codeph\">%</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tqs1665703533353__table_d18545e1_d18546e1_d18547e1__entry__2\">Match 0-<var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var> characters </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tqs1665703533353__table_d18545e1_d18546e1_d18547e1__entry__1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">?</code>  or <code class=\"ph codeph\">_</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tqs1665703533353__table_d18545e1_d18546e1_d18547e1__entry__2\">Match one character </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tqs1665703533353__table_d18545e1_d18546e1_d18547e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">!</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tqs1665703533353__table_d18545e1_d18546e1_d18547e1__entry__2\">Logical NOT </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tqs1665703533353__p_d176042e1_d176043e1_d176044e1\">Some operating systems attach their own interpretation to these characters, so using them can require special care. In some cases, your operating system provides a way of ensuring that wildcard characters are passed to Uniface without being interpreted by the operating system. Often, enclosing the parameters containing wildcards in double quotation marks (\") is effective.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tqs1665703533353__topic_d141137e1_d141138e1_d141139e1_d141140e1_d141141e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d364057e126\">\n                       \n Operating System Rules\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tqs1665703533353__p_d176048e1_d176049e1_d176050e1\">Observe the conventions of your operating system. Some of the information provided with parameters can be misunderstood by your operating system. For example, Unix does not recognize the logon information provided with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/log</span> switch unless you enclose the logon information in double quotation marks (\").</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hxc1665702744973.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Command Line Interface</a><p>Uniface provides a command line interface that enables you to access many functions without actually opening the user interface. By running a Uniface executable (such as ide.exe or uniface) with command line switches you can compile objects, debug applications, import and export, specify assignment files, and more.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532484\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532484\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Wildcards in Parameters Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 A number of the command line switches recognize a limited set of wildcards in parameters. Table 1. Wildcards for Parameters of Command Line Switches Wildcard Meaning * or % Match 0- n characters ? or _ Match one character ! Logical NOT Some operating systems attach their own interpretation to these characters, so using them can require special care. In some cases, your operating system provides a way of ensuring that wildcard characters are passed to Uniface without being interpreted by the operating system. Often, enclosing the parameters containing wildcards in double quotation marks (\") is effective. Operating System Rules Observe the conventions of your operating system. Some of the information provided with parameters can be misunderstood by your operating system. For example, Unix does not recognize the logon information provided with the /log switch unless you enclose the logon information in double quotation marks (\"). Related Links Uniface Command Line Interface Uniface provides a command line interface that enables you to access many functions without actually opening the user interface. By running a Uniface executable (such as ide.exe or uniface) with command line switches you can compile objects, debug applications, import and export, specify assignment files, and more. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}